    "css": "font-size: 30px",
    "text": "The 'globalUpdateRoutine' activates whenever any property of any widget changes.  Usually, you would want to restrict its exeuction to changes in a particular property.  To do that, specify the property at the beginning.  For example, 'textGlobalUpdateRoutine' will be called only when the `text` property of any widget changes.  In the example below, there is a leaderboard that is modified everytime the `'text' property changes.  You could accomplish the same thing by having a `textChangeRoutine` in each of the labels.  And with `globalUpdateRoutine` you should be careful that you understand times that it may be called that you were not anticipating.\n\nTo see the Leaderboard demo, change the scores and/or names in the labels below.\n\nThe JSON is in 'theBoard' widget with the tables of scores and names. "
